South African President Jacob Zuma on Monday night arrived at Jomo Kenyatta International Airport.Zuma, who came with First Lady Sizakele, was received by Foreign Affairs CS Amina Mohammed, Lands CS Jacob Kaimenyi and nominated Senator Zipporah Kittony. Foreign Affairs CS Amina Mohamed receiving South African First Lady Sizakele Zuma at JKIA on October 10, 2016. /COURTESYThe SA President is on a three-day State visit in Kenya. He will formally be received by President Uhuru Kenyatta on Tuesday.Zuma will receive a 21-gun salute and a guard of honour mounted by the Kenya Defence Forces at State House.Uhuru will then host Zuma for bilateral talks before addressing a joint press conference.South African President Jacob Zuma and Foreign Affairs CS Amina Mohamed at JKIA, October 10, 2016. /COURTESYOn Tuesday afternoon, the two heads of state will address a Kenya-South Africa business forum, before Zuma returns to State House for a banquet hosted in his honour.Uhuru and Zuma will sign agreements on trade, immigration, and security. The agreement will address non-tariff barriers and discuss ways to collaborate in security.